"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.13971,0.23938,0.17286,0.080989,0.066269,0.072379,0.049452,0.06281,0.035511,0.031479,0.02605,0.023116],"unified_progress":[0.11348,0.15532,0.13008,0.090199,0.083813,0.090292,0.069283,0.087489,0.05585,0.049669,0.041513,0.033008]},{"section":4,"text":"These symptoms lasted 20 minutes but improved after diphenhydramine.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.12391,0.20318,0.16094,0.098607,0.071495,0.07519,0.056131,0.066313,0.043952,0.039281,0.032074,0.02892],"unified_progress":[0.10927,0.13785,0.11297,0.10469,0.084139,0.08744,0.072462,0.083176,0.063583,0.056222,0.048623,0.039575]},{"section":5,"text":"Hmm, the key here is the symptoms and the medication.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.078845,0.11723,0.13104,0.12589,0.10356,0.080565,0.074034,0.066719,0.057614,0.06994,0.047529,0.047035],"unified_progress":[0.088032,0.079898,0.0842,0.09834,0.096991,0.090488,0.091434,0.086392,0.076989,0.090214,0.065178,0.051844]},{"section":6,"text":"Haloperidol is a typical antipsychotic, known for causing extrapyramidal side effects.","dimension":13,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.066626,0.099089,0.099732,0.10266,0.10166,0.09506,0.089761,0.083329,0.072802,0.071861,0.060211,0.057208],"unified_progress":[0.07819,0.070342,0.083421,0.088036,0.093402,0.097524,0.094137,0.093895,0.086044,0.083653,0.070795,0.060559]},{"section":7,"text":"The symptoms mentioned\u2014like oculogyric crisis, tongue protrusion, stiffness, and abnormal postures\u2014are classic signs of acute dystonia.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.062802,0.10495,0.096646,0.092034,0.091483,0.092795,0.088768,0.088616,0.077932,0.076212,0.066,0.06176],"unified_progress":[0.064455,0.08177,0.087214,0.08808,0.09088,0.095815,0.09195,0.094805,0.087978,0.083522,0.072736,0.060794]},{"section":8,"text":"Acute dystonia is an extrapyramidal reaction that can occur soon after starting antipsychotics, especially in younger patients.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046041,0.079173,0.086262,0.094047,0.098691,0.098526,0.098177,0.092647,0.083565,0.085008,0.070779,0.067083],"unified_progress":[0.052413,0.061142,0.08075,0.086504,0.092309,0.10168,0.098755,0.097991,0.093169,0.090725,0.07831,0.066248]},{"section":9,"text":"It usually happens within the first few days of treatment, which matches the 2 days here.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.054734,0.094264,0.09071,0.088731,0.089857,0.09349,0.090541,0.091408,0.083322,0.08258,0.072815,0.067549],"unified_progress":[0.064229,0.079613,0.081127,0.083953,0.087406,0.09169,0.090189,0.094433,0.089739,0.088621,0.079856,0.069144]},{"section":10,"text":"Diphenhydramine is an antihistamine with anticholinergic properties, and it's commonly used to treat these acute dystonic reactions.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047028,0.081104,0.087046,0.092322,0.095455,0.095775,0.09606,0.092665,0.084668,0.084854,0.073845,0.069178],"unified_progress":[0.053711,0.066053,0.081655,0.086509,0.092577,0.098488,0.096841,0.096166,0.092005,0.089333,0.07945,0.067213]},{"section":11,"text":"The fact that the symptoms resolved quickly after giving diphenhydramine supports that diagnosis.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052282,0.09003,0.09072,0.08912,0.08803,0.087996,0.087118,0.087663,0.083125,0.083763,0.077755,0.082396],"unified_progress":[0.057578,0.072511,0.076067,0.081986,0.085022,0.088461,0.088263,0.091564,0.090136,0.090523,0.089977,0.087912]},{"section":12,"text":"Other possibilities like neuroleptic malignant syndrome (NMS) come to mind, but NMS is more severe, has fever, rigidity, and autonomic instability, which aren't mentioned here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028287,0.061704,0.075275,0.085282,0.092458,0.096145,0.10242,0.10182,0.098508,0.09714,0.089243,0.07171],"unified_progress":[0.029898,0.055743,0.072395,0.080253,0.091431,0.097502,0.10034,0.10436,0.10387,0.10762,0.091104,0.065483]},{"section":13,"text":"Tardive dyskinesia is another movement disorder from antipsychotics, but that typically occurs after longer use, not so early.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02664,0.058033,0.071065,0.083545,0.093324,0.099496,0.10483,0.10405,0.098929,0.10044,0.087731,0.071915],"unified_progress":[0.032164,0.05457,0.071151,0.082316,0.091433,0.10113,0.10264,0.10661,0.1042,0.10528,0.086919,0.061586]},{"section":14,"text":"Oculogyric crisis can also be part of other conditions like tetanus, but the context of antipsychotic use points more to a drug-induced movement disorder.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028628,0.059603,0.072143,0.082925,0.091169,0.096321,0.10091,0.10059,0.098155,0.099756,0.089494,0.080311],"unified_progress":[0.036578,0.055786,0.070225,0.081314,0.089174,0.097074,0.099555,0.1024,0.10196,0.10232,0.090528,0.07309]},{"section":15,"text":"So, putting it all together, acute dystonia is the most likely diagnosis here.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029043,0.05278,0.062014,0.068674,0.073629,0.077094,0.083192,0.087273,0.09354,0.10013,0.10879,0.16385],"unified_progress":[0.030607,0.037093,0.04565,0.056308,0.061405,0.072749,0.07716,0.088247,0.097745,0.10753,0.14094,0.18457]}]}}